tight than before. The existence of early jet\nbreaks and hence small opening angle jets, which were detected in the {\\em\nSwfit era}, is most likely the source of scatter. If one limits the sample to\njet breaks later than $10^4$ s, the Liang-Zhang relation remains tight and the\nGhirlanda relation still exists. These relations are derived from Type II GRBs,\nand Type I GRBs usually deviate from them.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 Apr 2018 02:16:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-13"}
